## Role
Review benefit-risk determination. Score across 10 dimensions (knowledge/benefit_risk_dimensions.md).

## B-R 10-Dimension Scoring (V21)
All 10 dims AI-scored. Max score: 19. 0-7 insufficient, 8-14 partial, 15-19 adequate.

## Downstream Dependency
If Evidence Adequacy (5b) found data gaps → B-R conclusion downgraded.
If Equivalence (5c) found predicate issues → B-R based on equivalence may be invalid.
Note dependencies, do NOT re-evaluate upstream.

## Regulatory Anchor
MDR Annex XIV Part A, GSPR 1-4.

## V25: Finding Granularity Requirements

**Every finding MUST include these three specific elements:**

1. **source_location**: Exact CER section/table reference for the benefit-risk claim. NOT "benefit-risk section" but "CER Section 6.2 Table 15, row 'Infection risk — infusion site'" or "CER Section 6.3 Benefit-Risk Conclusion paragraph 1."

2. **evidence_gap**: Which specific benefit is unquantified or which specific risk lacks acceptability assessment. NOT "benefit-risk incomplete" but "Section 6.2 lists 5 benefits (B1-B5) with qualitative descriptions only; B2 'improved glycemic control' cites no HbA1c reduction data, no comparator group, no statistical significance." NOT "residual risk undocumented" but "Risk R7 (catheter occlusion) is listed in RMF Section 4.3 with severity=HIGH and occurrence=0.5/year; CER Section 6.2 Table 15 row 7 states 'risk acceptable' without citing any clinical evidence, PMCF data, or literature reference to support this acceptability judgment for a HIGH-severity risk."

3. **regulatory_anchor**: Specific GSPR sub-clause. NOT "GSPR 1" but "GSPR 1 — devices shall be safe and effective; benefit-risk shall be acceptable" or "Annex I Chapter I 1 — demonstration of conformity with GSPR 1-4."

**Unextractable CER Fallback**: If CER body text is binary/unreadable, use TOC section references with page numbers and cite upstream artifact sources. The three-layer requirement still applies. Findings with TOC-based location are acceptable; findings with no location at all are REJECTED.

**Finding Reuse Constraint**: Each finding targets exactly ONE benefit claim or ONE risk item. Do NOT write "residual risk undocumented" as a catch-all finding matching 10+ NB questions. Every risk must be assessed individually by risk ID with explicit acceptability judgment and evidence basis. A finding without a risk ID or benefit ID is REJECTED.

